  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "チョコボランド: A Game of Diceは、スクウェア・エニックスが開発した初のGBAタイトルで、ボードのようなマップ上で展開されます。サイコロを振ってチョコボを操作します。目的は、対戦相手からクリスタルポイントを奪って獲得することです。これらのポイントは、例えば魔女を購入するために使用でき、より多くのポイントを得るチャンスを増加させます。まさに資本主義の純粋な形です。",
      "lang": "ja",
      "source": "romu"
    },
    {
      "text": "Dice de Chocobo is a video game originally released in 1999 for the PlayStation in the Chocobo Collection. It was later planned to be remade for the WonderSwan Color, but was cancelled, and it was finally remade for the Game Boy Advance in 2002 and given the title Chocobo Land: A Game of Dice.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "igdb"
    },
    {
      "text": "The game is similar to Monopoly or even Fortune Street: The player has a certain amount of crystals that can be used to buy creatures to place on the board to increase the value of the space it is placed on. The player wins by accumulating the goal number of crystals and returning to the start panel.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "igdb_storyline"
    }
  ],
  "first_release_date": "2002-12-13",
